{{format-markdown "
### `keyboardLaxPriority`

By setting `keyboardLaxPriority` to `true`, you're saying that it will not block lower priority responders. This can help if you want a group of high level responders to always get a chance to handle key events without blocking the rest of your app. Note that all components within a given priority must have `keyboardLaxPriority` set to `true` or else the priority level will still block, as per usual.
"}}

